, {"authorId": "2320570554", "name": "Ke Xiao"}, {"authorId": "2340567663", "name": "Kexi Kang"}, {"authorId": "2342251777", "name": "Le Han"}, {"authorId": "2340018295", "name": "Leyang Wang"}, {"authorId": "2315068525", "name": "Lian-Chun Yu"}, {"authorId": "2261056712", "name": "Li Feng"}, {"authorId": "2152636027", "name": "Lin Zheng"}, {"authorId": "2266763355", "name": "Lin Chai"}, {"authorId": "2067369207", "name": "Longqiang Xing"}, {"authorId": "3237065", "name": "Meizhi Ju"}, {"authorId": "2340030679", "name": "Mingyuan Chi"}, {"authorId": "12554337", "name": "Mozhi Zhang"}, {"authorId": "2261407452", "name": "Pei‐Yu Huang"}, {"authorId": "2105541235", "name": "Peng-Xia Niu"}, {"authorId": "2144902519", "name": "Pengfei Li"}, {"authorId": "2321683265", "name": "Pengyu Zhao"}, {"authorId": "2339724140", "name": "Qi Yang"}, {"authorId": "2340177257", "name": "Qidi Xu"}, {"authorId": "2376286649", "name": "Qiexiang Wang"}, {"authorId": "2340182716", "name": "Qin Wang"}, {"authorId": "2374331289", "name": "Qiuhui Li"}, {"authorId": "2308039623", "name": "Ruitao Leng"}, {"authorId": "2340474488", "name": "Shengmin Shi"}, {"authorId": "2184021679", "name": "Shu Yu"}, {"authorId": "2334996672", "name": "Si-si Li"}, {"authorId": "2220129714", "name": "S. Zhu"}, {"authorId": "2299736380", "name": "Tao Huang"}, {"authorId": "2340032935", "name": "Tianrun Liang"}, {"authorId": "2225238340", "name": "Weigao Sun"}, {"authorId": "2296851156", "name": "Wei-Bing Sun"}, {"authorId": "2342248270", "name": "Weiyu Cheng"}, {"authorId": "2340169645", "name": "Wenkai Li"}, {"authorId": "2340138103", "name": "Xiangjun Song"}, {"authorId": "2262205128", "name": "Xiaojuan Su"}, {"authorId": "2299550737", "name": "Xiaodong Han"}, {"authorId": "2211878698", "name": "Xinjie Zhang"}, {"authorId": "2283269460", "name": "Xi-Yong Hou"}, {"authorId": "2340030930", "name": "Xu Min"}, {"authorId": "2340473606", "name": "Xun Zou"}, {"authorId": "2116517206", "name": "Xuyang Shen"}, {"authorId": "2287529989", "name": "Yan Gong"}, {"authorId": "2369157792", "name": "Yin-Bo Zhu"}, {"authorId": "2299107208", "name": "Yipeng Zhou"}, {"authorId": "2266275708", "name": "Yiran Zhong"}, {"authorId": "2140880461", "name": "Yong Hu"}, {"authorId": "2340353405", "name": "Yuanxiang Fan"}, {"authorId": "2328658653", "name": "Yue Yu"}, {"authorId": "2340153548", "name": "Yufeng Yang"}, {"authorId": "2144442088", "name": "Yuhao Li"}, {"authorId": "2340168196", "name": "Yunan Huang"}, {"authorId": "2340174031", "name": "Yunji Li"}, {"authorId": "2339710094", "name": "Yunpeng Huang"}, {"authorId": "2269756654", "name": "Yun Xu"}, {"authorId": "2331578319", "name": "Yuxin Mao"}, {"authorId": "2340117566", "name": "Zehan Li"}, {"authorId": "2109965103", "name": "Zekang Li"}, {"authorId": "2340118960", "name": "Zewei Tao"}, {"authorId": "2106685689", "name": "Ze Ying"}, {"authorId": "2276526242", "name": "Zhaoyang Cong"}, {"authorId": "2330163267", "name": "Zhen Qin"}, {"authorId": "2334523170", "name": "Zhe-yu Fan"}, {"authorId": "2340549278", "name": "Zhihang Yu"}, {"authorId": "2340180351", "name": "Zhuo Jiang"}, {"authorId": "2340167212", "name": "Zijia Wu"}], "abstract": "We introduce MiniMax-01 series, including MiniMax-Text-01 and MiniMax-VL-01, which are comparable to top-tier models while offering superior capabilities in processing longer contexts. The core lies in lightning attention and its efficient scaling. To maximize computational capacity, we integrate it with Mixture of Experts (MoE), creating a model with 32 experts and 456 billion total parameters, of which 45.9 billion are activated for each token. We develop an optimized parallel strategy and highly efficient computation-communication overlap techniques for MoE and lightning attention. This approach enables us to conduct efficient training and inference on models with hundreds of billions of parameters across contexts spanning millions of tokens. The context window of MiniMax-Text-01 can reach up to 1 million tokens during training and extrapolate to 4 million tokens during inference at an affordable cost. Our vision-language model, MiniMax-VL-01 is built through continued training with 512 billion vision-language tokens. Experiments on both standard and in-house benchmarks show that our models match the performance of state-of-the-art models like GPT-4o and Claude-3.5-Sonnet while offering 20-32 times longer context window. We publicly release MiniMax-01 at https://github.com/MiniMax-AI."}, {"paperId": "41d08becd3eef1cc1e25de359deb42bb6b74c088", "externalIds": {"DOI": "10.1021/acsami.5c13537", "CorpusId": 281251168, "PubMed": "40931514"}, "publicationVenue": {"id": "850fc070-bb53-4d7e-87ef-5e94e6f107de", "name": "ACS Applied Materials and Interfaces", "type": "journal", "alternate_names": ["AC Appl Mater Interface", "AC Appl Mater  Interface", "ACS Applied Materials & Interfaces"], "issn": "1944-8244", "url": "https://pubs.acs.org/journal/aamick", "alternate_urls": ["http://pubs.acs.org/journal/aamick", "https://pubs.acs.org/loi/aamick"]}, "url": "https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/41d08becd3eef1cc1e25de359deb42bb6b74c088", "title": "Chargeable Hydrogels with Dual Modulatory Effects of Bacterial Killing and Immune Remodeling toward Wound Healing.", "venue": "ACS Applied Materials and Interfaces", "year": 2025, "isOpenAccess": false, "openAccessPdf": {"url": "", "status": null, "license": null, "disclaimer": "Notice: Paper or abstract available at https://api.unpaywall.org/v2/10.1021/acsami.5c13537?email=<INSERT_YOUR_EMAIL> or https://doi.org/10.1021/acsami.5c13537, which is subject to the license by the author or copyright owner provided with this content. Please go to the source to verify the license and copyright information for your use."}, "journal": {"name": "ACS applied materials & interfaces"}, "authors": [{"authorId": "2368435266", "name": "Yiheng Tang"}, {"authorId": "2367482869", "name": "Guopeng Xu"}, {"authorId": "2380363086", "name": "Jing Liu"}, {"authorId": "3722142", "name": "Jiezhou Wu"}, {"authorId": "2387133485", "name": "Jingyang Fang"}, {"authorId": "2380006799", "name": "Shengji Gu"}, {"authorId": "2162636535", "name": "Wenyan Zhang"}, {"authorId": "2367477001", "name": "Wenkun Zhang"}, {"authorId": "2117230934", "name": "Junfeng Hu"}, {"authorId": "2238730040", "name": "Paul. K. Chu"}, {"authorId": "2149077132", "name": "Jianzhong Du"}, {"authorId": "2028214101", "name": "Guomin Wang"}], "abstract": "Wound infections challenge clinical medicine, and developing novel therapies is critically important in overcoming antimicrobial resistance and an off-balanced immune microenvironment. Electrical stimulation as a biocompatible, easy-to-operate, and controllable technique has great potential in eradicating pathogens and modulating the immune system. However, safe and soft platforms that integrate both bactericidal and immunological modulatory effects of electrical stimulation are rarely reported. In this study, we propose a new strategy targeting infectious wound healing that utilizes chargeable hydrogels as the carrier of electrical stimulation to deploy timely bacterial disinfection and subsequently reprogram the macrophage phenotype. The chargeable platform (AT-PP@MnO2) is constructed by doping manganese dioxide (MnO2) microparticles into acid-treated PEDOT:PSS hydrogels (AT-PP), in which MnO2 acts as the collector for charge storage and release. Upon a safe charging process at 0.8 V, AT-PP@MnO2 achieves 99% bacterial inactivation within 15 min. The bactericidal mechanism is attributed to charging-evoked electron deprivation from bacteria, inducing an intracellular reactive oxygen species (ROS) burst to damage bacterial structure. Furthermore, the in vivo mouse model of wound infection demonstrates that AT-PP@MnO2 can timely eradicate invasive bacteria to prevent infection from aggravation and then reprogram macrophages from proinflammatory to anti-inflammatory for immune remodeling, thus achieving nearly 100% wound healing within 14 days. This study introduces an emerging physical paradigm to the design of multifunctional wound dressing, offering broad potential in combating bacterial infections and immune modulation."}, {"paperId": "caa6bc28a77fe3f7eb38d76193a63cb7c24d261a", "externalIds": {"DOI": "10.1016/j.scitotenv.2022.153666", "CorpusId": 246839407, "PubMed": "35176378"}, "publicationVenue": {"id": "6bc10a15-943a-45d8-af37-996d0b52574e", "name": "Science of the Total Environment", "type": "journal", "alternate_names": ["Science of The Total Environment", "Sci Total Environ"], "issn": "0048-9697", "url": "http://www.elsevier.com/wps/find/journaldescription.cws_home/503360/description#description", "alternate_urls": ["https://www.journals.elsevier.com/science-of-the-total-environment/", "http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/00489697"]}, "url": "https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/caa6bc28a77fe3f7eb38d76193a63cb7c24d261a", "title": "A collective statement in support of saving pangolins.", "venue": "Science of the Total Environment", "year": 2022, "isOpenAccess": true, "openAccessPdf": {"url": "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.scitotenv.2022.153666", "status": "HYBRID", "license": "CCBYNCND", "disclaimer": "Notice: Paper or abstract available at https://api.unpaywall.org/v2/10.1016/j.scitotenv.2022.153666?email=<INSERT_YOUR_EMAIL> or https://doi.org/10.1016/j.scitotenv.2022.153666, which is subject to the license by the author or copyright owner provided with this content. Please go to the source to verify the license and copyright information for your use."}, "journal": {"name": "The Science of the total environment", "pages": "\n          153666\n        "}, "authors": [{"authorId": "2642325", "name": "S. Choo"}, {"authorId": "46254189", "name": "J. L. Chong"}, {"authorId": "2661310", "name": "P. Gaubert"}, {"authorId": "2082382371", "name": "A. C. Hughes"}, {"authorId": "2111361625", "name": "Stephen O'Brien"}, {"authorId": "47438050", "name": "A. Ch